body:
Comment 6 by **tarqe39**: 
Oh, this seem to be an old installation that I forgot about. I have made a clean
installation of GO 1.2rc3 and MinGW and retried to make packages. It was successful. The
problem was probably that version 1.2rc3 was trying to reference packages from an older
version so it resulted in undefined reference.

Thank you very much, Alex!
